document_notes.text:
This update for e2fsprogs fixes the following issues:

Security issue fixed:

- CVE-2019-5094: Fixed an arbitrary code execution via specially crafted ext4 file systems. (bsc#1152101)

Non-security issue fixed:

- libext2fs: Call fsync(2) to clear stale errors for a new a unix I/O channel. (bsc#1145716)

notes.text: An exploitable code execution vulnerability exists in the quota file functionality of E2fsprogs 1.45.3. A specially crafted ext4 partition can cause an out-of-bounds write on the heap, resulting in code execution. An attacker can corrupt a partition to trigger this vulnerability.
